task.summary: - added constructors to allow passing in config instead of from system properties - greatly reduced use of static fields and methods, use final where possible - use logging library (log4j) instead of system.out - code formatting / modernization: - use braces around 1-line if statements - use foreach loops - synchronization when opening new stream and when reading/writing to stream in daemon mode - added junit and basic unit test - fixed bug in splitting tag name/value, didn't work when value contained a colon - updated Tag.parseValue() to allow returning a Double when the source value is a fraction (e.g. 1/4)
- added startUp() method to allow calling externally - new shutDown() method is an alias for existing close()
added logging during iterations to show activity
no camelcase on startup() and shutdown()
corrected for loop to start on 1 for logging purposes
catch "Stream closed" IOException that occurs if daemon process has exited, try restarting the daemon
